featured_reviews.review_id:
Ashraful Masjid is a beautiful mosque that happens to be about 196 years old. It is situated in the heart of the city Amroha which is 130 km eastern side of the national capital of India. It is beautifully ornamented with traditional motives created by experts of the year 1825. Consisting of the main hall with two tall minarets measuring 80 ft and a courtyard. The ceiling of this about to be a 200-year-old mosque is a masterpiece of fine craftsmanship.

Haji Sheikh Ashraf Ali was from Azeemabad a village near Amroha. He was a rich person and in his advent in Amroha, was mesmerised by the climate and calmness of this city. He finally decided to stay in Amroha.

According to the history of the city, Amroha Ashraful Masjid was constructed by Haji Sheikh Ashraf Ali in the year 1825 CE or 1241 Hijri according to the Islamic calendar. This mosque was then constructed single-handedly. The architect of this present marvellous building was Dildar Hussain Mistry Lakhnavi, who commenced the work in the year 1866 expanding the then Ashraful Masjid which was a small mosque then. The ornamental work of this mosque was carried out in the year 1883 CE or 1300 Hijri by Imam-e-Jumma (Chief Cleric) Moulana Aulad Hasan.

Written by
Nadeem Naqvi

featured_reviews.review_id:
Masjid Ashraful masajid       (msjd 'shrf lmsjd)
This Shia Jama masjid, commonly known as Ashraf ul masajid, is one of the largest mosques in Amroha. Initially it was built in 1825/hj1241 by Haji Sheikh Ashraf Ali of Azeemabad. This Masjid was constructed just adjacent to Dewankhana in the premises of Mahal built after the name of Meer Syed Mohammad Shafaat. This mahal was a complex consisting a mehal Sarai,Dewan khana and a Jama masjid. Later on Dewan khana was converted into a Azakhana ( Imambada mm brr) which is now known as Azakhana Mohallah Shafatpota.
Due to the increasing numbers of momineen in Masjid,it was felt that this mosque should have been extended. However a committee of prominent Shia personalities of Amroha was formed and they decided to collect the contributions from all momineen of Amroha for reconstruction of Jama masjid. So Jama masjid was extended and rebuilt in 1867/hj 1284 and it was named as Masjid Ashraf ul masajid in memory of Haji Sheikh Ashraf Ali.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Mazar of Hazrat Khuwaja Shah Abdul Hadi Siddiqui Chishti is located at Akbarpur Patti road, about half an mile away from Northwestern neighborhood of Amroha.
There are lots of mango trees and dense forest all around this historically important dargah complex consisting an old mosque, Mazar , cemetery, khanqah and a well. It is located in an atmosphere of spirituality and tranquility with a superb outside location. The worthwhile efforts in maintaining the natural atmosphere in the vicinity of this dargah complex may be appreciated .
As per records available in " Kishware Aulia,"(khshwr wly mrwhh) written by Ahmed Hussain Siddiqui , "Hazrat Shah Abdul Hadi Siddiqui ( one of the descendent of Hazrat Mohammed Ibn Abu Bakr Siddiq ) was born in 14 Rajab,1042 AH" . He died on 4th Ramazan, 1190 AH and was buried in the village Kharee Khera in Bareilly. After some time , his coffin  was shifted to Amroha and again buried in his own garden.
